content.description: Start climbing up the water groove. Do some long pulls on pockets. Interesting crux matching and moving off a not so great hold. Climbing gets easier after crux.
content.location: Located on the River wall. To the left of Float Trip and to the right of Egyptian Conniption. Shares the same start as Congo Spray, but heads right at the third bolt.

content.description: This route starts on the left main face of the X Block and goes up the arete for 2 bolts. Then head left to finish up XOXO
content.location: Left side of X Block

content.description: Goes up the arete.
content.location: On the right arete of the south face of the X Block.

content.description: Great warm up for the harder routes in the area.  A little thin at the start and continuous.
content.location: Located just around the left arete of the south face of the X Block.

content.description: This route begins on Generator X but breaks left at the 5th bolt and heads through steeper terrain.

content.location: 12 feet left of Xterminator (2nd route left on X Block).

content.description: Starts at the same point as "Slave Labor" and "Carpal Tunnel". Stay with the left line.
content.location: Mass Production wall. 20 feet left of "Assembly Line".

content.description: This route climbs up the dark streak slab. Probably also pretty dirty!
content.location: This route is directly to the right of the route “Delirious” on the other wall, and to the left of the route “Mystical Season”.

content.description: Seemingly impossible start leading up to some unique climbing on typical Jackson slab holds. Some may consider hard for the grade.
content.location: the first climb on the wall to the left of the belay ledge, left of team honda

content.description: Enjoy your ride up the wall on good positive holds.
content.location: Located directely to the right of “Killer Chickens” and to the left of “Spectator Sport”.

content.description: Start on small holds and move up the overhanging face with large holds and larger moves. Cruise the roof to the chains.
content.protection: 7 bolts, 6 have fixed draws, 2 bolt chain anchor with fixed carabiners.
content.location: This route is down left and around the arete from fashionably late. The route is the just before the detached ledge.

content.description: This route is tricky! Keep your eyes peeled for hidden holds.
content.location: Starts to the right of Four Bettys, and to the left of Three Day Impression.

content.description: Climb up the pocketed face.
content.location: This route is directly to the right of “Traffic Jam” and to the left of “Delirius”.

content.description: Climb up the bulging face.
content.location: Found on the Salemander Butteress. Found in between the routes “Gecko” on the left, and “Chameleon” on the right.

content.description: Climb up the sandy face. Don’t get tricked into going the wrong direction!
content.location: This is he last route on the right of the Salemander Buttress.

content.description: A neat boulder problem gets you to a steep roof. Move through the "Jackson Falls Jugs" in the roof to a deadpoint gaining the face and easier climbing to the anchors
content.location: On the left side of the section of the main wall that bulges out like some sort of pillar. Just right of Delirious.

content.description: Begin on the left angling crack, but cut right and follow the furthest right bolt line. The crux is between bolt 2 and 3. But it’s not over till you clip the chains.

Start with an interesting vertical crux to a good rest before big moves and sustained climbing through overhanging rock to hero jugs. A 13a variation goes up the arete to the right, bypassing the beginning crux. Listed as the Pipe Dream Project in Vertical Heartland.
content.location: On the right side of the overhanging main wall in front of the large spectator boulder

content.description: This ones a little thuggy, with a dynamic move for the crux. You end up linking up with Team Honda near the top.
content.location: The route directly to the right of Team Honda.

content.description: Shares the same start as “Hubba Hubba”, but you break left and follow the red streak at the 4th bolt.
content.location: Shares the same start as “Hubba Hubba”, break left at the 4th bolt. Found between “Pool of Reflection” on the right, and “Circle in the Round” on the left.

content.description: Tough climbing leads to a extremely severe crux. I’ve been told the crux sequence is about v10 alone. Luckily after the crux it’s gets significantly easier on he way to the chains.
content.location: The route with a couple perma draws directly to the right of “Float Trip”.

content.description: Start standing on the boulder to start the juggy traverse. The jugs run out when you pull yourself onto the head wall.
content.location: Begins on top of the boulder directly to the left of Balance of Power.

content.description: Climb the crack and either end at the anchors or top out through the right gully.
content.location: The middle of the wall to the left of Four Bettys Wall.

content.description: Climb up the left angling crack until I️t stops. Proceed to climb up the face.
content.protection: 8 bolts. Stick clip the first bolt
content.location: Shares the same start as Poseur and Hoser.

content.description: Starts at the same point as "Carpal Tunnel" and "Workshop". Veer right after first clip.
content.location: Mass Production wall. 20 feet left of "Assembly Line".

content.description: Climb up the left-facing flake until it runs out. Then move right and over the bulge.
content.location: This is the route closest to the arete on the left hand side of the wall. It can be found to the left of “Traffic Jam”.

content.description: Climb up the lime green streak near the gully.
content.location: The route directly to the right of “Jarred’s Route” and to the left of “Dupuy Conqueror”.

content.description: An interesting start leads to the first roof. Spend some time to figure out how to get in position to pull the roof. Don’t get comfortable! The climbing only gets harder for every bulge you pull.
content.location: The route directly to the right of “Remove La Ropa” and directly to the left of “Key Lime”.

content.description: Fight through the low crux at the first bolt to gain the steep sustained face.
content.location: Between “Pool of Reflection” and “Circle in the Round”. Shares the same start as “Ooh La La”.

content.description: This one is a little bit easier than Poseur. Climb up the middle line. Crux is a litttle thuggy and near the middle of the climb.
content.protection: 7 bolts. Stick clip the first bolt.
content.location: Middle line between Last Gasp of Hope and Poseur.

content.description: Pumpy.
content.location: Leftmost route on the south face of the X Block (10 feet left of X Factor).

content.description: Climb up the pocketed face on the left side of the buttress.
content.location: The left most rote on the Salemander Buttress. Located directly left of the route “Skink”.

content.description: Pure jackson fun, sloppers and all!
content.location: The bolt line in the middle of Four Bettys Face Wall, (the wall to the left of X Block).

content.description: Start with a moderate boulder problem to get from the ground to the second bolt. The crux sequence is between the 3rd and the 5th bolt.
content.location: Located to the left of “The Nile” and to the right of “Zambezi”.

content.description: Very fun, slightly technical pockets up a vertical face to an over hanging jug finish
content.location: Main Wall

content.description: The freed start to the old aid start of EOP. Pull down hard on a slightly crumbly, compression boulder problem at the start into EOP. End at single bolt anchor. A project continues up and right.
Start by aiding your way to the first bolt. Once in place, pull a long move to the lip and proceed to pull on sloping holds to a hard dead point move to a jug. Finish on easier terrain afterwords.
content.location: To the right of Balance of Power, and to the left of Remove La Rope.

content.description: A low sever crux leads to easier terrain above.
content.location: The route directly to the left of “Congo Spray”.

content.description: Climb up the golden streaked face.
content.location: On the left most side of the main wall. Starts to the left of “Circle in the Round”.

content.description: A variation of the route “Pool of Reflection”. Start around the corner to the right, and join in at the 4th bolt.
content.location: Starts around the corner to the right of “Pool of Reflection”.

content.description: This route climbs up the arete on the right side of the wall, next to the chimney.
content.location: This route is directly to the right of “Spectator Sport” and to the left on the wall to the right “Victoria’s Secret”.

content.description: Same start as Zambezi. Cut left after the second bolt to climb Congo Spray. The crux is right at the third bolt.
content.location: Same start as Zambezi, cut left at the second bolt. Located to the right of Egyptian Conniption and to the left of Float Trip.

content.description: Low crux leads to sustained climbing.
content.location: Found between the routes “Duppy Conqueror” on the left and “Ooh La La” on the right.

content.description: This route starts off running with a low crux. Continue up the face using what sandy holds you can find. Shares the same anchors as “Salamander”.
content.location: Found on the Salemander Buttress. This route is located in between the two routes “Skink” on the left, and “Salemander” on the right.

content.description: Starts at the same point as "Slave Labor" and "Workshop". Take the middle line after the 2nd clip.
content.location: Mass Production wall. 20 feet left of "Assembly Line".

content.description: Climb up the pocketed arete that leads to a committing slab above.
content.location: The route directly to the right of “Pinocchio Theory” and to the left of “Fashionably Late”.

climbs.name: Big Chaw
climbs.fa: Mike Balossi, Darrell Sauer, Jeff Stockton 2002

content.description: Hard to read finish
content.location: Mass Production wall. It's about 30 feet left of "Slave Labor", "Carpal Tunnel" and "Workshop".

content.description: Start the route off by pulling on a couple small pockets, and a hard lock off move/drive by. The climbing gets easier, but it’s not over till you clip the anchors.
content.location: The rite directly to the right of “Fashionably Late”.

content.description: Very tall aesthetic route, with great movement.
content.location: The second route to the left of Remove La Ropa.

content.description: Two difficult, technical cruxes on razor crimps separated by a section of more moderate climbing. Not for those afraid of a little blood.
content.location: From "Candy Corner" (5.7), go left to the Mass Production Wall, and then 15 feet left again.

content.description: Begin on the platform, climb up the beautiful Black and Tan face. Keep your eye out for the drilled mono.
content.protection: 6 bolts. Stick clip the first bolt!
content.location: Left most line on the Black and Tan wall. To the left of Last Gasp of Hope.

content.description: Interesting face climbing to the right of an arete leads to a nice rest, where you cross to the other side of the arete and tackle several classic Jackson-style bulges.
In the shade for most of the day, Classic routes, worth the walk!
